The Wallet app lives right on your iPhone. It’s where you securely keep your credit and debit cards, eligible driver’s license or state ID, transit cards, keys, event tickets, and more — all in one place. And it all works with iPhone or Apple Watch, so you can take less with you but always bring more.

Apple Pay
Apple Pay is an easy, secure way to pay in stores or online.1 Pay for a ride, a pizza, or even a new sofa — with Touch ID or Face ID.

Apple Card
Apple Card is the credit card created by Apple. You earn up to 3% unlimited Daily Cash back on every purchase every day, and it’s designed with all the privacy and security you’d expect from Apple. You can apply in as little as minute with no impact to your credit score.2
 
Apple Cash
Apple Cash is an easy and secure way to send and receive money in Messages or Wallet.3  And because it’s a digital card that lives in Wallet, you can use it to make purchases in stores, online, or in apps with Apple Pay. With Tap to Cash, you can send and receive Apple Cash simply by holding your iPhone near someone else’s iPhone — without having to share phone numbers.

Driver’s License and State ID
Add your eligible driver’s license or state ID to Wallet, and with just a tap of your iPhone or Apple Watch you can present your ID without handing over your device.4 The security of Face ID and Touch ID means only you can present your ID.

Boarding Passes
After you add your airline passes to Wallet, just show up at your gate and easily present your pass directly from your lock screen. And receive timely flight information and notifications along the way.5

Transit
Set your card to Express Mode, then just tap and hop on to ride the next train or bus.5 Breeze through the turnstiles by holding your iPhone or Apple Watch to the reader. 

Sports & Live Events
With Wallet, your tickets are always at the ready. Enter a concert venue, sports stadium or festival with just your iPhone or Apple Watch.5 Tickets in Apple Wallet now bring fans a richer experience including venue maps, recommended Apple Music playlists, and more.

Keys
Store keys to your car, home, workplace, and hotel room in Wallet.5 Unlock doors with just a tap of your iPhone or Apple Watch, and securely share keys in Wallet through messaging apps, including Messages, Mail, and more.

Loyalty and Rewards
Add your favorite coffee shop, drugstore, or retail rewards cards to Wallet, and next time you’re at checkout, just tap and pay to receive and redeem rewards.5

Editing tools like trim, replace, and the new “Save As” feature let you fine-tune your recordings without altering the original. The transcription feature converts speech into text, simplifying the process of finding and referencing specific content. And the new feature to record a vocal layer on top of an existing instrumental recording* without the need for headphones making it easy to capture song ideas on the go. Users can then separate and edit the vocal and instrumental layers independently to continue expanding on those ideas. And with iCloud support, you can capture audio on the go with your iOS device, then use your Mac to do even more with your recordings.

Features

Record
• Record using the built-in microphone, a Bluetooth headset, or a compatible external microphone.
• Choose uncompressed audio for maximum sound fidelity, ensuring the highest quality recordings.
• Opt for compressed audio to save storage space and record longer sessions.
• Automatically name recordings based on your location.
• Record a vocal layer* over an instrumental track without headphones.
• Stereo recording adds greater depth and dimension to your audio**.
• iCloud support keeps your recordings and edits in sync across all your devices, including iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch, Mac, and Vision Pro.

Edit
• Pinch-to-zoom for more precision when editing.
• Trim your recordings to save just the portion you want.
• Replace and resume to fine-tune your recordings.
• Save As lets you make edits and save them as a new recording without altering the original file.
• Separate and independently edit the vocal and instrumental takes for layered recordings*.
• Transcripts automatically convert speech into text for easy reference***.
• Enhance Recording reduces background noise and room reverberation with a single tap.

Organize
• Quickly find recordings with the search feature.
• Folders make it easy to organize your recordings.
• Mark recordings as Favorites so you can quickly access them later.

Listen and share
• Speed up or slow down playback of your recordings, or jump 15 seconds forward or back.
• Skip Silence analyzes your recordings and automatically skips over gaps in your audio.
• Share multiple recordings at once via AirDrop, Mail, Messages, and more.
• Import vocal layer* recordings into Logic Pro as a two-track project for advanced editing and production.

* Adding a vocal layer on top of a Voice Memos recording is available only on the iPhone 16 Pro models.
** Stereo recording requires Apple devices equipped with stereo microphones and iOS 18 or later.
*** Audio transcription is available on iPhone 12 and later in English (Australia), English (Canada), English (Ireland), English (New Zealand), English (South Africa), English (UK), and English (US).
